---
import '../../assets/styles/WhatImUpToNow.css';

const entries = [
  {
    platform: 'Shopify',
    badge: 'Current Client',
    date: '2023 – Present',
    title: 'Atelier Dacko — Custom Jewelry E-Commerce Storefront',
    body: [
      `I've built and maintained Atelier Dacko's Shopify storefront over three project phases spanning 2+ years — starting from a WordPress portfolio site and evolving into a 14+ page e-commerce storefront with 200+ product SKUs serving 500+ monthly visitors.`,
      `Key deliverables include an interactive ring builder that lets customers configure stone, band, and size selections (replacing manual quote requests), custom Liquid templates, Stripe payment integration, and ongoing feature development and client communication as sole developer.`,
    ],
    tags: ['Shopify', 'Liquid', 'Stripe', 'WordPress', 'Elementor', 'SEO', 'Responsive Design'],
  },
  {
    platform: 'HubSpot CMS',
    badge: 'Completed',
    date: '2025',
    title: 'AI Agency — Custom HubSpot Theme & Legacy Migration',
    body: [
      `For this unnamed client, an AI-focused agency, I developed a custom HubSpot theme with 8 pages from the ground up. The project involved managing the full migration from their legacy theme to the new custom build — mapping existing content, restructuring page templates, and building reusable HubL modules with custom CSS and JavaScript components.`,
      `I configured Google Tag Manager analytics for tracking and focused heavily on performance — achieving 90+ PageSpeed scores and a 30% improvement in page load speed through image optimization, lazy loading, and caching configuration. The theme was architected for scalability, with plans to expand into additional service pages and blog integration.`,
    ],
    tags: ['HubSpot', 'HubL', 'Custom Theme', 'Google Tag Manager', 'JavaScript', 'CSS', 'Migration'],
  },
  {
    platform: 'Shopify',
    badge: 'Completed',
    date: '2023',
    title: 'Geeked Out Goods — Vintage Gaming E-Commerce Components',
    body: [
      `Geeked Out Goods was my first freelance client — a vintage gaming retailer looking to improve their Shopify storefront. I built custom Shopify components and Liquid templates, implementing product display modules and collection page layouts that better showcased their inventory.`,
      `A key part of the project was executing JSON data migrations to restructure their 400+ item product catalog, along with performing security hardening and technical SEO audits to improve search visibility. This project laid the foundation for my Shopify and Liquid development workflow.`,
    ],
    tags: ['Shopify', 'Liquid', 'JSON', 'Data Migration', 'SEO Audits', 'Security'],
  },
];
---

<div class="now-section-wrapper">
  <div class="now-section-header">
    <h2>What I'm Up To Now</h2>
    <p>
      Since graduating, I've been building production websites for real clients across WordPress,
      HubSpot, and Shopify — here's a closer look at each project and the work involved.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="now-entries">
    {entries.map((entry) => (
      <article class="now-entry">
        <div class="now-entry-meta">
          <span class="now-entry-badge">{entry.badge}</span>
          <span class="now-entry-date">{entry.date}</span>
        </div>
        <h3>{entry.title}</h3>
        <div class="now-entry-body">
          {entry.body.map((paragraph) => (
            <p>{paragraph}</p>
          ))}
        </div>
        <div class="now-entry-tags">
          {entry.tags.map((tag) => (
            <span class="now-tag">{tag}</span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </article>
    ))}
  </div>
</div>
